ShefRobot

Class Motor

  • java.lang.Object
    • ShefRobot.Motor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Runnable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    LargeMotor, MediumMotor

    public abstract class Motor
extends Object
    This class represents a generic motor, it is must be instantiated as a subclass of the correct motor model (Large or Medium). This allows the motor objects to be calibrated correctly. Any methods called on the same Motor will occur in order unless a method is otherwise stated as being asynchronous
    See Also:
    Robot.getLargeMotor(Motor.Port), Robot.getMediumMotor(Motor.Port)

      • setSpeed

        public void setSpeed(int newSpeed)
        Sets the speed of the Motor. If the motor is already moving, forward() or backward() must be called after. The lowest accepted value is 0 The motors maximum speed can be found using getMaxSpeed()
        Parameters:
        newSpeed - The speed of the motor, this value must not be negative
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - When newSpeed is negative

      • getMaxSpeed

        public int getMaxSpeed()
        Returns the maximum speed, this value is based off the Robots battery voltage (it decreases as the Robots battery drains). A charged robot should be able to reach a speed of atleast 700
        Returns:
        The current maximum speed of the robot

      • rotate

        public void rotate(int degrees,
                   boolean async)
        Rotates the motor the specified number of degrees. Negative values will cause the motor to rotate backwards. When async is set to true, this method will return instantly, this can be used if you need to call rotate multiple motors simultaneously.
        Parameters:
        degrees - The number of degrees that the motor should rotate
        async - When true this method will not wait for the action to complete before returning control

      • rotateTo

        public void rotateTo(int degrees)
        Rotates the motor to the specified tacho count. After this action has completed, getTachoCount() should return the specified value within 2 degrees.
        Parameters:
        degrees - The tacho count to rotate the motor until
        See Also:
        rotateTo(int, boolean)

      • rotateTo

        public void rotateTo(int degrees,
                     boolean async)
        Rotates the motor to the specified tacho count. After this action has completed, getTachoCount() should return the specified value within 2 degrees. When async is set to true, this method will return instantly, this can be used if you need to call rotate multiple motors simultaneously.
        Parameters:
        degrees - The tacho count to rotate the motor until
        async - When true this method will not wait for the action to complete before returning control
